Enum Constant Detail

EvalModeReady

public static final RedLaserExtras.RLScannerReadyState EvalModeReady
Scanning will work, but the SDK considers itself to be in 'Eval' mode, meaning this app is not licensed, and will only function for a limited number of scans. If you get this and you're expecting to be in Licensed mode, check that the license file is in the right place.

LicensedModeReady

public static final RedLaserExtras.RLScannerReadyState LicensedModeReady
License file was found, verified, and it marks this app as licensed. This is the 'good to go' result..

APILevelTooLow

public static final RedLaserExtras.RLScannerReadyState APILevelTooLow
The device doesn't meet the SDK's minimum API level requirement. Currently, the SDK requires API level 7, but this minimum could be increased in the future. Instead of checking for API level 7 yourself, it's better to call checkReadyStatus and be prepared for this result.

NoCamera

public static final RedLaserExtras.RLScannerReadyState NoCamera
This is a convenience result for devices that don't have cameras. You could check for this yourself, but it's easier to use checkReadyStatus--you should be calling this method anyway.

BadLicense

public static final RedLaserExtras.RLScannerReadyState BadLicense
This means the license file was found, but either failed digital signature verification or didn't contain an entry matching your application's root classname. There's a couple of other reasons this result could happen for specific license types, but they all fall into "The license was found, but doesn't authorize this app to run."

ScanLimitReached

public static final RedLaserExtras.RLScannerReadyState ScanLimitReached
When running in Evaluation mode, the SDK will stop working after 25 scans, and checkReadyStatus will start returning this result code.

MissingPermissions

public static final RedLaserExtras.RLScannerReadyState MissingPermissions
Your application must enable specific permissions in order to use the SDK. See the pdf documentation that comes with the SDK.

UnsupportedHardware

public static final RedLaserExtras.RLScannerReadyState UnsupportedHardware
Some Android hardware just doesn't seem to work right. This enum was created for the Motorola Xoom, which kernel panics when we ask the camera to do almost anything. Other hardware may return this result in the future as well. If checkReadyStatus returns this result you should treat it similarly to the 'NoCamera' result, unless you're sure the SDK really will work on the current device.

UnknownState

public static final RedLaserExtras.RLScannerReadyState UnknownState
This is the result code that should not ever happen--if you see this, please tell us, we need to fix it.
